definition:
Please answer in JSON format: What does '{word}' mean? Return the content structure as follows:

{
  "correctedWord": "standard word (same as original if no correction needed)",
  "phonetic": "IPA transcription (use International Phonetic Alphabet standard, e.g., /sɛ̃tʁ/)",
  "definitions": [
    {
      "partOfSpeech": "part of speech (must use English: noun, verb, adjective, adverb, pronoun, preposition, conjunction, interjection, article, numeral, auxiliary, determiner, etc.)",
      "definition": "English definition",
      "examples": [
        {
          "french": "French example sentence (use French original text)",
          "english": "English translation of the example"
        }
      ]
    }
    // Multiple objects can be listed if there are multiple parts of speech
  ],
  "slangMeaning": null,
  "phraseExplanation": null
}

Requirements:
- All definitions and explanations must be in English.
- Phonetic must use IPA (International Phonetic Alphabet), not French pronunciation rules (e.g., centre → /sɛ̃tʁ/).
- French examples must use French original text (e.g., Je vais au centre-ville).
- Example translations must be in English.
- Part of speech must use English terms (noun, verb, adjective, etc.), not French terms (nom, verbe, adjectif, etc.)
- Return only JSON, no extra content.
- Important: The user has provided the word '{word}', please process it directly and return the JSON result.
